A vigilante operative identified simply as Monday, in Otokutu Community, Ughelli South council area of Delta State, has reportedly stabbed one Omezu Martins to death. It was gathered that the incident happened last Wednesday evening. Though details of the incident were not clear at press time, it was learnt that the vigilante man had gone to settle a dispute between his friend and the deceased. Sources claimed that the misunderstanding between the duo was almost leading to a fight when the vigilante member suddenly stabbed Martins in the chest. The victim was reportedly rushed to a hospital within the area, but he later died. In another development, unknown gunmen shot dead two persons in Sedeco, Uvwie council area of the state. The Nation gathered that the incident occurred on Thursday evening. Acting spokesperson of the state police command Edafe Bright confirmed both incidents to The Nation on telephone. “I can confirm the vigilante issue and the other one. And the DPOs are investigating,” he said.